12,LGBT,lgbt,Genève,CH,1504043665000,"

Calling all queer runners! We are a new LGBTQ group that organises running sessions for people of any fitness level, in diverse locations in and around Geneva. The group is an official member of the worldwide Frontrunners organisation for gay, lesbian, bisexual, trans, intersex, and queer-identifying people who are enthusiastic about jogging.

Meetup training sessions will be once or twice per week (possibly less in winter) and flexible in terms of distance and speed. Occasional trail running on Saleve and in the Jura is also scheduled for the warmer months.

All meetup training sessions are logged using the MapMyRun application and shared on our Facebook profile geneva.frontrunners.3

https://www.facebook.com/geneva.frontrunners.3
Participation is voluntary. Frontrunners claims no liability for injuries or accidents that may occur during club activities and events. Insurance is the responsibility of participants / members.

12,LGBT,lgbt,Zürich,CH,1426692533000,"

This is a group for LGBT Professionals in Zurich who wish to meet other LGBT's for networking, sharing ideas, good conversation and making new friends.
We are the largest most active mixed international group in Switzerland and we welcome Lesbian, Gay, Bisexual &
column2: Transgender. We bring all LGBT Professionals together!

column1: We meet every month at a cool venue, normally on the third Wednesday or Thursday of each month.
Our group was founded in March 2015. Since then we have grown at a phenomenal rate. We have a range and diversity of characters in our group and we always have a fun time together.
We operate a membership system and invite guests to join us &
column2: try us out first before enrolling as a full member.&nbsp
column3: Guests can attend two events only before we ask you to join our group as a ‘life member’.

column1: Our 'life members' enjoy access to our groups in Zurich, Geneva, Basel, Lugano &
column2: London. We are adding more cities in the future!

column1: New members wishing to join must be referred by an existing ‘founder member’ or ‘life member’ of our group.
We have our regular mid month networking event, lunches, brunches, dinners, city tours, bar tours, art events, comedy nights, club nights &
- Join in! Feel free to message us with any questions and we look forward to meeting you.

column2: never miss our news or an event:- www.facebook.com/zurichlgbtprofessionals

column1: Please ensure you have a face picture in your profile. We reserve the right to decline membership of our group if you do not have a clear face picture.
When requesting permission to join our group you need to include in your profile a link to one of your social media profiles. Either Linkedin, Facebook or Twitter.

column3: inactive members may be deleted from our group as we are a serious group for serious like minded people.&nbsp

column1: We look forward to meeting you soon!

12,LGBT,lgbt,Zürich,CH,1479755568000,"

Hello, this Meetup is for anyone who dreams of, interested in the idea of, plans to, wants terribly to... share a house with other people under the rainbow flag. It means living fully and openly as who you are, regardless of sexual orientation, gender expression, underwear color. I have had several house sharing experiences, and I love it. I just wish I could live with LGBTQ people and their allies. As this is more fun!!
This Meetup is to get people who are interested in this idea to meet, talk about their project, their vision of a house, their lifestyle and rythme. I personally wish I would live in a house that welcomes languages such as english-german-french, non-smoking, with educated crowd, with an interest in living green and organic. But you might have your own idea of a house-share? Let's meet!!

Perhaps you’d like more quality non-sexual touch in your life, or perhaps you just love to cuddle at every opportunity. Come along, meet good people, learn about (and experience) the importance of touch, and have fun. Hold and Cuddle is a structured event which explores affection, intimacy, boundaries and verbal/non-verbal communication. The evening is strictliy non-sexual so that you can relax and
column2: meet men in a fun and warm-hearted environment.

column1: Sehnst Du Dich manchmal auch nach nicht sexuellen Berührungen, sondern Geborgenheit, Gehalten Werden, Innigkeit? Oder vielleicht bist Du einfach ein Mann der gerne kuschelt – Kuschelbär? Dann schau rein, triff tolle Männer, erfahre, lerne, erlebe die Wichtigkeit von Körperberührungen, Körperkontakt und fühl Dich einfach wohl.

column2: Cuddle ist ein strukturierter Anlass an dem wir Zuneigung, Intimität, Grenzen erkennen und respektieren, gemeinsam entdecken und erleben. Hold &amp
column4: Du kannst Dich entspannen, Geben und Nehmen in spielerischer –&nbsp

12,LGBT,lgbt,Windisch,CH,1515623191000,"

Hello :) I am a gay woman from the UK, and I want to meet some people from the LGBT+ community who live in Aargau. I live in Windisch, near Brugg, with my German wife. I think it's important that we have more in common than just being LGBT+, and I imagine that we could find common activities, have discussions, and work on projects together. To start off, I would like to know who is interested and what your ideas are! I'm very friendly, and can speak English, German, and French.

Hoi! Ich bin eine lesbische Frau, die aus Grossbritannien kommt, und ich will Leute kennenlernen, die LSBTQ sind und in Aargau wohnen. Ich wohne in Windisch, neben Brugg, mit meiner deutschen Frau. Ich glaube, es ist wichtig, nicht nur LSBTQ Leute zu kennen, sondern auch weitere Gemeinsamkeiten zu haben, und ich stelle mir vor, dass wir gemeinsame Aktivitäten, Diskussionen, und Projekte machen könnten. Am Anfang, will ich einfach wissen, wen es gibt, und was eure Ideen sind! Ich bin sehr freundlich, und kann Englisch, Deutsch, und Französisch sprechen.

12,LGBT,lgbt,Zürich,CH,1426692533000,"

This is a group for LGBT Professionals in Zurich who wish to meet other LGBT's for networking, sharing ideas, good conversation and making new friends.
We are the largest most active mixed international group in Switzerland and we welcome Lesbian, Gay, Bisexual &
column2: Transgender. We bring all LGBT Professionals together!

column1: We meet every month at a cool venue, normally on the third Wednesday or Thursday of each month.
Our group was founded in March 2015. Since then we have grown at a phenomenal rate. We have a range and diversity of characters in our group and we always have a fun time together.
We operate a membership system and invite guests to join us &
column2: try us out first before enrolling as a full member.&nbsp
column3: Guests can attend two events only before we ask you to join our group as a ‘life member’.

column1: Our 'life members' enjoy access to our groups in Zurich, Geneva, Basel, Lugano &
column2: London. We are adding more cities in the future!

column1: New members wishing to join must be referred by an existing ‘founder member’ or ‘life member’ of our group.
We have our regular mid month networking event, lunches, brunches, dinners, city tours, bar tours, art events, comedy nights, club nights &
- Join in! Feel free to message us with any questions and we look forward to meeting you.

column2: never miss our news or an event:- www.facebook.com/zurichlgbtprofessionals

column1: Please ensure you have a face picture in your profile. We reserve the right to decline membership of our group if you do not have a clear face picture.
When requesting permission to join our group you need to include in your profile a link to one of your social media profiles. Either Linkedin, Facebook or Twitter.

column3: inactive members may be deleted from our group as we are a serious group for serious like minded people.&nbsp

column1: We look forward to meeting you soon!

12,LGBT,lgbt,Zürich,CH,1479755568000,"

Hello, this Meetup is for anyone who dreams of, interested in the idea of, plans to, wants terribly to... share a house with other people under the rainbow flag. It means living fully and openly as who you are, regardless of sexual orientation, gender expression, underwear color. I have had several house sharing experiences, and I love it. I just wish I could live with LGBTQ people and their allies. As this is more fun!!
This Meetup is to get people who are interested in this idea to meet, talk about their project, their vision of a house, their lifestyle and rythme. I personally wish I would live in a house that welcomes languages such as english-german-french, non-smoking, with educated crowd, with an interest in living green and organic. But you might have your own idea of a house-share? Let's meet!!

12,LGBT,lgbt,Zürich,CH,1491587687000,"

Perhaps you’d like more quality non-sexual touch in your life, or perhaps you just love to cuddle at every opportunity. Come along, meet good people, learn about (and experience) the importance of touch, and have fun. Hold and Cuddle is a structured event which explores affection, intimacy, boundaries and verbal/non-verbal communication. The evening is strictliy non-sexual so that you can relax and
column2: meet men in a fun and warm-hearted environment.

column1: Sehnst Du Dich manchmal auch nach nicht sexuellen Berührungen, sondern Geborgenheit, Gehalten Werden, Innigkeit? Oder vielleicht bist Du einfach ein Mann der gerne kuschelt – Kuschelbär? Dann schau rein, triff tolle Männer, erfahre, lerne, erlebe die Wichtigkeit von Körperberührungen, Körperkontakt und fühl Dich einfach wohl.

12,LGBT,lgbt,Windisch,CH,1515623191000,"

Hello :) I am a gay woman from the UK, and I want to meet some people from the LGBT+ community who live in Aargau. I live in Windisch, near Brugg, with my German wife. I think it's important that we have more in common than just being LGBT+, and I imagine that we could find common activities, have discussions, and work on projects together. To start off, I would like to know who is interested and what your ideas are! I'm very friendly, and can speak English, German, and French.

Hoi! Ich bin eine lesbische Frau, die aus Grossbritannien kommt, und ich will Leute kennenlernen, die LSBTQ sind und in Aargau wohnen. Ich wohne in Windisch, neben Brugg, mit meiner deutschen Frau. Ich glaube, es ist wichtig, nicht nur LSBTQ Leute zu kennen, sondern auch weitere Gemeinsamkeiten zu haben, und ich stelle mir vor, dass wir gemeinsame Aktivitäten, Diskussionen, und Projekte machen könnten. Am Anfang, will ich einfach wissen, wen es gibt, und was eure Ideen sind! Ich bin sehr freundlich, und kann Englisch, Deutsch, und Französisch sprechen.

12,LGBT,lgbt,Zürich,CH,1426692533000,"

This is a group for LGBT Professionals in Zurich who wish to meet other LGBT's for networking, sharing ideas, good conversation and making new friends.
We are the largest most active mixed international group in Switzerland and we welcome Lesbian, Gay, Bisexual &
column2: Transgender. We bring all LGBT Professionals together!

column1: We meet every month at a cool venue, normally on the third Wednesday or Thursday of each month.
Our group was founded in March 2015. Since then we have grown at a phenomenal rate. We have a range and diversity of characters in our group and we always have a fun time together.
We operate a membership system and invite guests to join us &
column2: try us out first before enrolling as a full member.&nbsp
column3: Guests can attend two events only before we ask you to join our group as a ‘life member’.

column1: Our 'life members' enjoy access to our groups in Zurich, Geneva, Basel, Lugano &
column2: London. We are adding more cities in the future!

column1: New members wishing to join must be referred by an existing ‘founder member’ or ‘life member’ of our group.
We have our regular mid month networking event, lunches, brunches, dinners, city tours, bar tours, art events, comedy nights, club nights &
- Join in! Feel free to message us with any questions and we look forward to meeting you.

column2: never miss our news or an event:- www.facebook.com/zurichlgbtprofessionals

column1: Please ensure you have a face picture in your profile. We reserve the right to decline membership of our group if you do not have a clear face picture.
When requesting permission to join our group you need to include in your profile a link to one of your social media profiles. Either Linkedin, Facebook or Twitter.

column3: inactive members may be deleted from our group as we are a serious group for serious like minded people.&nbsp

column1: We look forward to meeting you soon!

Zwischen Juni und Mitte Oktober bietet der Gay Sport Zürich Trans* &
column2: Queer* Menschen am Montagabend zwei Bahnen zum freien Schwimmen an. Alle Geschlechter und Geschlechtsidentitäten sind willkommen – unabhängig von Transitionsstand oder Transitionsabsichten. Fühlt euch frei, jene Badebekleidung zu tragen, in der ihr euch am wohlsten fühlt, ob Lycra-Shirt oder weite Badehose ist einerlei! Hauptsache, keine Strassenbekleidung.

12,LGBT,lgbt,Zürich,CH,1479755568000,"

Hello, this Meetup is for anyone who dreams of, interested in the idea of, plans to, wants terribly to... share a house with other people under the rainbow flag. It means living fully and openly as who you are, regardless of sexual orientation, gender expression, underwear color. I have had several house sharing experiences, and I love it. I just wish I could live with LGBTQ people and their allies. As this is more fun!!
This Meetup is to get people who are interested in this idea to meet, talk about their project, their vision of a house, their lifestyle and rythme. I personally wish I would live in a house that welcomes languages such as english-german-french, non-smoking, with educated crowd, with an interest in living green and organic. But you might have your own idea of a house-share? Let's meet!!

Perhaps you’d like more quality non-sexual touch in your life, or perhaps you just love to cuddle at every opportunity. Come along, meet good people, learn about (and experience) the importance of touch, and have fun. Hold and Cuddle is a structured event which explores affection, intimacy, boundaries and verbal/non-verbal communication. The evening is strictliy non-sexual so that you can relax and
column2: meet men in a fun and warm-hearted environment.

column1: Sehnst Du Dich manchmal auch nach nicht sexuellen Berührungen, sondern Geborgenheit, Gehalten Werden, Innigkeit? Oder vielleicht bist Du einfach ein Mann der gerne kuschelt – Kuschelbär? Dann schau rein, triff tolle Männer, erfahre, lerne, erlebe die Wichtigkeit von Körperberührungen, Körperkontakt und fühl Dich einfach wohl.

column2: Cuddle ist ein strukturierter Anlass an dem wir Zuneigung, Intimität, Grenzen erkennen und respektieren, gemeinsam entdecken und erleben. Hold &amp
column4: Du kannst Dich entspannen, Geben und Nehmen in spielerischer –&nbsp

12,LGBT,lgbt,Sankt Gallen,CH,1504468687000,"

Wenn du an einem Treffen kommen möchtest, bitten wir dich an der Versanstaltung mit Gesichtsfoto und Namen anzumelden, wir möchten sehen, wer es ist, der/die kommen möchte.

Du kannst selber bei deinen Profileinstellungen hier einstellen, ob man deine Interessen sehen kann oder nicht, das ist dir überlassen. Das ist eine private Gruppe, d.h. interessierte Meetup Mitglieder können den Inhalt dieses Meetups nur teilweise einsehen, bevor sie beitreten. Nicht-Mitglieder
column3: Veranstaltungsorte, Beschreibungen, Mitgliederlisten, Gruppenprofile, Teilnehmer, Fotos oder andere geteilte Inhalte. Datenschutz, Verbindlichkeit ist uns wichtig.

column1: Unsere Geschichte: Am Herbst 2017 waren wir hier in St Gallen ein schwuler Mann und eine Bi Frau, die sich noch von Zürich aus gekannt haben, und sie haben beide das Bedürfnis gehabt, zusammen durch Gebet in ihrem persönlichem Leben gestärkt zu werden.
column2: Beide sind von evangelikalem, sprich pfingstlichem, charismatischem Hintergrund, sie kamen informell an der Militärkantine in St. Gallen an einer Bank sitzend zusammen um zu beten.<span>&nbsp
column3: Sie kannten ähnliche, LGBT christliche Gruppen in anderen Städten, in der ""Zwischenraum"" Bewegung aber eben noch nicht in St Gallen, oder in der Ostschweiz.&nbsp
column4: Sie meinten, es wäre doch schön ein regelmässiges Treffen, bzw. Community für ähnlich gesinnte zu haben. So kam es dann zur meetup Gründung, und dann kam es zum ersten Treffen im September 2017 mit erst 3, am zweiten mal 7 Leuten, Frauen und Männer, der Rest ist Geschichte.

column1: Die Vision ist eine christliche LGBT Gruppe in St Gallen zu haben, die im Gebet ihren Fokus hat, uns gegenseitig im Glauben, in Christus zu stärken, und Jünger sein. Genau :)

column1: Unsere Geschichte: Am Herbst 2017 waren wir hier in St Gallen ein schwuler Mann und eine Bi Frau, die sich noch von Zürich aus gekannt haben, und sie haben beide das Bedürfnis gehabt, zusammen durch Gebet in ihrem persönlichem Leben gestärkt zu werden.
column2: Beide sind von evangelikalem, sprich pfingstlichem, charismatischem Hintergrund, sie kamen informell an der Militärkantine in St. Gallen an einer Bank sitzend zusammen um zu beten.<span>&nbsp
column3: Sie kannten ähnliche, LGBT christliche Gruppen in anderen Städten, in der ""Zwischenraum"" Bewegung aber eben noch nicht in St Gallen, oder in der Ostschweiz.&nbsp
column4: Sie meinten, es wäre doch schön ein regelmässiges Treffen, bzw. Community für ähnlich gesinnte zu haben. So kam es dann zur meetup Gründung, und dann kam es zum ersten Treffen im September 2017 mit erst 3, am zweiten mal 7 Leuten, Frauen und Männer, der Rest ist Geschichte.

column1: Die Vision ist eine christliche LGBT Gruppe in St Gallen zu haben, die im Gebet ihren Fokus hat, uns gegenseitig im Glauben, in Christus zu stärken, und Jünger sein. Genau :)

12,LGBT,lgbt,Windisch,CH,1515623191000,"

Hello :) I am a gay woman from the UK, and I want to meet some people from the LGBT+ community who live in Aargau. I live in Windisch, near Brugg, with my German wife. I think it's important that we have more in common than just being LGBT+, and I imagine that we could find common activities, have discussions, and work on projects together. To start off, I would like to know who is interested and what your ideas are! I'm very friendly, and can speak English, German, and French.

Hoi! Ich bin eine lesbische Frau, die aus Grossbritannien kommt, und ich will Leute kennenlernen, die LSBTQ sind und in Aargau wohnen. Ich wohne in Windisch, neben Brugg, mit meiner deutschen Frau. Ich glaube, es ist wichtig, nicht nur LSBTQ Leute zu kennen, sondern auch weitere Gemeinsamkeiten zu haben, und ich stelle mir vor, dass wir gemeinsame Aktivitäten, Diskussionen, und Projekte machen könnten. Am Anfang, will ich einfach wissen, wen es gibt, und was eure Ideen sind! Ich bin sehr freundlich, und kann Englisch, Deutsch, und Französisch sprechen.

12,LGBT,lgbt,Zürich,CH,1426692533000,"

This is a group for LGBT Professionals in Zurich who wish to meet other LGBT's for networking, sharing ideas, good conversation and making new friends.
We are the largest most active mixed international group in Switzerland and we welcome Lesbian, Gay, Bisexual &
column2: Transgender. We bring all LGBT Professionals together!

column1: We meet every month at a cool venue, normally on the third Wednesday or Thursday of each month.
Our group was founded in March 2015. Since then we have grown at a phenomenal rate. We have a range and diversity of characters in our group and we always have a fun time together.
We operate a membership system and invite guests to join us &
column2: try us out first before enrolling as a full member.&nbsp
column3: Guests can attend two events only before we ask you to join our group as a ‘life member’.

column1: Our 'life members' enjoy access to our groups in Zurich, Geneva, Basel, Lugano &
column2: London. We are adding more cities in the future!

column1: New members wishing to join must be referred by an existing ‘founder member’ or ‘life member’ of our group.
We have our regular mid month networking event, lunches, brunches, dinners, city tours, bar tours, art events, comedy nights, club nights &
- Join in! Feel free to message us with any questions and we look forward to meeting you.

column2: never miss our news or an event:- www.facebook.com/zurichlgbtprofessionals

column1: Please ensure you have a face picture in your profile. We reserve the right to decline membership of our group if you do not have a clear face picture.
When requesting permission to join our group you need to include in your profile a link to one of your social media profiles. Either Linkedin, Facebook or Twitter.

column3: inactive members may be deleted from our group as we are a serious group for serious like minded people.&nbsp

column1: We look forward to meeting you soon!

Hello, this Meetup is for anyone who dreams of, interested in the idea of, plans to, wants terribly to... share a house with other people under the rainbow flag. It means living fully and openly as who you are, regardless of sexual orientation, gender expression, underwear color. I have had several house sharing experiences, and I love it. I just wish I could live with LGBTQ people and their allies. As this is more fun!!
This Meetup is to get people who are interested in this idea to meet, talk about their project, their vision of a house, their lifestyle and rythme. I personally wish I would live in a house that welcomes languages such as english-german-french, non-smoking, with educated crowd, with an interest in living green and organic. But you might have your own idea of a house-share? Let's meet!!

Perhaps you’d like more quality non-sexual touch in your life, or perhaps you just love to cuddle at every opportunity. Come along, meet good people, learn about (and experience) the importance of touch, and have fun. Hold and Cuddle is a structured event which explores affection, intimacy, boundaries and verbal/non-verbal communication. The evening is strictliy non-sexual so that you can relax and
column2: meet men in a fun and warm-hearted environment.

column1: Sehnst Du Dich manchmal auch nach nicht sexuellen Berührungen, sondern Geborgenheit, Gehalten Werden, Innigkeit? Oder vielleicht bist Du einfach ein Mann der gerne kuschelt – Kuschelbär? Dann schau rein, triff tolle Männer, erfahre, lerne, erlebe die Wichtigkeit von Körperberührungen, Körperkontakt und fühl Dich einfach wohl.

12,LGBT,lgbt,Windisch,CH,1515623191000,"

Hello :) I am a gay woman from the UK, and I want to meet some people from the LGBT+ community who live in Aargau. I live in Windisch, near Brugg, with my German wife. I think it's important that we have more in common than just being LGBT+, and I imagine that we could find common activities, have discussions, and work on projects together. To start off, I would like to know who is interested and what your ideas are! I'm very friendly, and can speak English, German, and French.

Hoi! Ich bin eine lesbische Frau, die aus Grossbritannien kommt, und ich will Leute kennenlernen, die LSBTQ sind und in Aargau wohnen. Ich wohne in Windisch, neben Brugg, mit meiner deutschen Frau. Ich glaube, es ist wichtig, nicht nur LSBTQ Leute zu kennen, sondern auch weitere Gemeinsamkeiten zu haben, und ich stelle mir vor, dass wir gemeinsame Aktivitäten, Diskussionen, und Projekte machen könnten. Am Anfang, will ich einfach wissen, wen es gibt, und was eure Ideen sind! Ich bin sehr freundlich, und kann Englisch, Deutsch, und Französisch sprechen.

12,LGBT,lgbt,Zürich,CH,1426692533000,"

This is a group for LGBT Professionals in Zurich who wish to meet other LGBT's for networking, sharing ideas, good conversation and making new friends.
We are the largest most active mixed international group in Switzerland and we welcome Lesbian, Gay, Bisexual &
column2: Transgender. We bring all LGBT Professionals together!

column1: We meet every month at a cool venue, normally on the third Wednesday or Thursday of each month.
Our group was founded in March 2015. Since then we have grown at a phenomenal rate. We have a range and diversity of characters in our group and we always have a fun time together.
We operate a membership system and invite guests to join us &
column2: try us out first before enrolling as a full member.&nbsp
column3: Guests can attend two events only before we ask you to join our group as a ‘life member’.

column1: Our 'life members' enjoy access to our groups in Zurich, Geneva, Basel, Lugano &
column2: London. We are adding more cities in the future!

column1: New members wishing to join must be referred by an existing ‘founder member’ or ‘life member’ of our group.
We have our regular mid month networking event, lunches, brunches, dinners, city tours, bar tours, art events, comedy nights, club nights &
- Join in! Feel free to message us with any questions and we look forward to meeting you.

column2: never miss our news or an event:- www.facebook.com/zurichlgbtprofessionals

column1: Please ensure you have a face picture in your profile. We reserve the right to decline membership of our group if you do not have a clear face picture.
When requesting permission to join our group you need to include in your profile a link to one of your social media profiles. Either Linkedin, Facebook or Twitter.

column3: inactive members may be deleted from our group as we are a serious group for serious like minded people.&nbsp

column1: We look forward to meeting you soon!

Queer women (bisexual, lesbian, pansexual, trans, cis, genderqueer, etc.) are invited to join us for fun and friendly social gatherings.
Let's enjoy each other's company, share some laughs, and have a good time.

12,LGBT,lgbt,Zürich,CH,1479755568000,"

Hello, this Meetup is for anyone who dreams of, interested in the idea of, plans to, wants terribly to... share a house with other people under the rainbow flag. It means living fully and openly as who you are, regardless of sexual orientation, gender expression, underwear color. I have had several house sharing experiences, and I love it. I just wish I could live with LGBTQ people and their allies. As this is more fun!!
This Meetup is to get people who are interested in this idea to meet, talk about their project, their vision of a house, their lifestyle and rythme. I personally wish I would live in a house that welcomes languages such as english-german-french, non-smoking, with educated crowd, with an interest in living green and organic. But you might have your own idea of a house-share? Let's meet!!

12,LGBT,lgbt,Windisch,CH,1515623191000,"

Hello :) I am a gay woman from the UK, and I want to meet some people from the LGBT+ community who live in Aargau. I live in Windisch, near Brugg, with my German wife. I think it's important that we have more in common than just being LGBT+, and I imagine that we could find common activities, have discussions, and work on projects together. To start off, I would like to know who is interested and what your ideas are! I'm very friendly, and can speak English, German, and French.

Hoi! Ich bin eine lesbische Frau, die aus Grossbritannien kommt, und ich will Leute kennenlernen, die LSBTQ sind und in Aargau wohnen. Ich wohne in Windisch, neben Brugg, mit meiner deutschen Frau. Ich glaube, es ist wichtig, nicht nur LSBTQ Leute zu kennen, sondern auch weitere Gemeinsamkeiten zu haben, und ich stelle mir vor, dass wir gemeinsame Aktivitäten, Diskussionen, und Projekte machen könnten. Am Anfang, will ich einfach wissen, wen es gibt, und was eure Ideen sind! Ich bin sehr freundlich, und kann Englisch, Deutsch, und Französisch sprechen.

12,LGBT,lgbt,Zürich,CH,1426692533000,"

This is a group for LGBT Professionals in Zurich who wish to meet other LGBT's for networking, sharing ideas, good conversation and making new friends.
We are the largest most active mixed international group in Switzerland and we welcome Lesbian, Gay, Bisexual &
column2: Transgender. We bring all LGBT Professionals together!

column1: We meet every month at a cool venue, normally on the third Wednesday or Thursday of each month.
Our group was founded in March 2015. Since then we have grown at a phenomenal rate. We have a range and diversity of characters in our group and we always have a fun time together.
We operate a membership system and invite guests to join us &
column2: try us out first before enrolling as a full member.&nbsp
column3: Guests can attend two events only before we ask you to join our group as a ‘life member’.

column1: Our 'life members' enjoy access to our groups in Zurich, Geneva, Basel, Lugano &
column2: London. We are adding more cities in the future!

column1: New members wishing to join must be referred by an existing ‘founder member’ or ‘life member’ of our group.
We have our regular mid month networking event, lunches, brunches, dinners, city tours, bar tours, art events, comedy nights, club nights &
- Join in! Feel free to message us with any questions and we look forward to meeting you.

column2: never miss our news or an event:- www.facebook.com/zurichlgbtprofessionals

column1: Please ensure you have a face picture in your profile. We reserve the right to decline membership of our group if you do not have a clear face picture.
When requesting permission to join our group you need to include in your profile a link to one of your social media profiles. Either Linkedin, Facebook or Twitter.

column3: inactive members may be deleted from our group as we are a serious group for serious like minded people.&nbsp

12,LGBT,lgbt,Zürich,CH,1479755568000,"

Hello, this Meetup is for anyone who dreams of, interested in the idea of, plans to, wants terribly to... share a house with other people under the rainbow flag. It means living fully and openly as who you are, regardless of sexual orientation, gender expression, underwear color. I have had several house sharing experiences, and I love it. I just wish I could live with LGBTQ people and their allies. As this is more fun!!
This Meetup is to get people who are interested in this idea to meet, talk about their project, their vision of a house, their lifestyle and rythme. I personally wish I would live in a house that welcomes languages such as english-german-french, non-smoking, with educated crowd, with an interest in living green and organic. But you might have your own idea of a house-share? Let's meet!!

Perhaps you’d like more quality non-sexual touch in your life, or perhaps you just love to cuddle at every opportunity. Come along, meet good people, learn about (and experience) the importance of touch, and have fun. Hold and Cuddle is a structured event which explores affection, intimacy, boundaries and verbal/non-verbal communication. The evening is strictliy non-sexual so that you can relax and
column2: meet men in a fun and warm-hearted environment.

12,LGBT,lgbt,Windisch,CH,1515623191000,"

Hello :) I am a gay woman from the UK, and I want to meet some people from the LGBT+ community who live in Aargau. I live in Windisch, near Brugg, with my German wife. I think it's important that we have more in common than just being LGBT+, and I imagine that we could find common activities, have discussions, and work on projects together. To start off, I would like to know who is interested and what your ideas are! I'm very friendly, and can speak English, German, and French.

Hoi! Ich bin eine lesbische Frau, die aus Grossbritannien kommt, und ich will Leute kennenlernen, die LSBTQ sind und in Aargau wohnen. Ich wohne in Windisch, neben Brugg, mit meiner deutschen Frau. Ich glaube, es ist wichtig, nicht nur LSBTQ Leute zu kennen, sondern auch weitere Gemeinsamkeiten zu haben, und ich stelle mir vor, dass wir gemeinsame Aktivitäten, Diskussionen, und Projekte machen könnten. Am Anfang, will ich einfach wissen, wen es gibt, und was eure Ideen sind! Ich bin sehr freundlich, und kann Englisch, Deutsch, und Französisch sprechen.

12,LGBT,lgbt,Zürich,CH,1426692533000,"

This is a group for LGBT Professionals in Zurich who wish to meet other LGBT's for networking, sharing ideas, good conversation and making new friends.
We are the largest most active mixed international group in Switzerland and we welcome Lesbian, Gay, Bisexual &
column2: Transgender. We bring all LGBT Professionals together!

column1: We meet every month at a cool venue, normally on the third Wednesday or Thursday of each month.
Our group was founded in March 2015. Since then we have grown at a phenomenal rate. We have a range and diversity of characters in our group and we always have a fun time together.
We operate a membership system and invite guests to join us &
column2: try us out first before enrolling as a full member.&nbsp
column3: Guests can attend two events only before we ask you to join our group as a ‘life member’.

column1: Our 'life members' enjoy access to our groups in Zurich, Geneva, Basel, Lugano &
column2: London. We are adding more cities in the future!

column1: New members wishing to join must be referred by an existing ‘founder member’ or ‘life member’ of our group.
We have our regular mid month networking event, lunches, brunches, dinners, city tours, bar tours, art events, comedy nights, club nights &
- Join in! Feel free to message us with any questions and we look forward to meeting you.

column2: never miss our news or an event:- www.facebook.com/zurichlgbtprofessionals

column1: Please ensure you have a face picture in your profile. We reserve the right to decline membership of our group if you do not have a clear face picture.
When requesting permission to join our group you need to include in your profile a link to one of your social media profiles. Either Linkedin, Facebook or Twitter.

column3: inactive members may be deleted from our group as we are a serious group for serious like minded people.&nbsp

column1: We look forward to meeting you soon!

Hello, this Meetup is for anyone who dreams of, interested in the idea of, plans to, wants terribly to... share a house with other people under the rainbow flag. It means living fully and openly as who you are, regardless of sexual orientation, gender expression, underwear color. I have had several house sharing experiences, and I love it. I just wish I could live with LGBTQ people and their allies. As this is more fun!!
This Meetup is to get people who are interested in this idea to meet, talk about their project, their vision of a house, their lifestyle and rythme. I personally wish I would live in a house that welcomes languages such as english-german-french, non-smoking, with educated crowd, with an interest in living green and organic. But you might have your own idea of a house-share? Let's meet!!

Perhaps you’d like more quality non-sexual touch in your life, or perhaps you just love to cuddle at every opportunity. Come along, meet good people, learn about (and experience) the importance of touch, and have fun. Hold and Cuddle is a structured event which explores affection, intimacy, boundaries and verbal/non-verbal communication. The evening is strictliy non-sexual so that you can relax and
column2: meet men in a fun and warm-hearted environment.

column1: Sehnst Du Dich manchmal auch nach nicht sexuellen Berührungen, sondern Geborgenheit, Gehalten Werden, Innigkeit? Oder vielleicht bist Du einfach ein Mann der gerne kuschelt – Kuschelbär? Dann schau rein, triff tolle Männer, erfahre, lerne, erlebe die Wichtigkeit von Körperberührungen, Körperkontakt und fühl Dich einfach wohl.

column2: Cuddle ist ein strukturierter Anlass an dem wir Zuneigung, Intimität, Grenzen erkennen und respektieren, gemeinsam entdecken und erleben. Hold &amp

12,LGBT,lgbt,Windisch,CH,1515623191000,"

Hello :) I am a gay woman from the UK, and I want to meet some people from the LGBT+ community who live in Aargau. I live in Windisch, near Brugg, with my German wife. I think it's important that we have more in common than just being LGBT+, and I imagine that we could find common activities, have discussions, and work on projects together. To start off, I would like to know who is interested and what your ideas are! I'm very friendly, and can speak English, German, and French.

Hoi! Ich bin eine lesbische Frau, die aus Grossbritannien kommt, und ich will Leute kennenlernen, die LSBTQ sind und in Aargau wohnen. Ich wohne in Windisch, neben Brugg, mit meiner deutschen Frau. Ich glaube, es ist wichtig, nicht nur LSBTQ Leute zu kennen, sondern auch weitere Gemeinsamkeiten zu haben, und ich stelle mir vor, dass wir gemeinsame Aktivitäten, Diskussionen, und Projekte machen könnten. Am Anfang, will ich einfach wissen, wen es gibt, und was eure Ideen sind! Ich bin sehr freundlich, und kann Englisch, Deutsch, und Französisch sprechen.

12,LGBT,lgbt,Zürich,CH,1426692533000,"

This is a group for LGBT Professionals in Zurich who wish to meet other LGBT's for networking, sharing ideas, good conversation and making new friends.
We are the largest most active mixed international group in Switzerland and we welcome Lesbian, Gay, Bisexual &
column2: Transgender. We bring all LGBT Professionals together!

column1: We meet every month at a cool venue, normally on the third Wednesday or Thursday of each month.
Our group was founded in March 2015. Since then we have grown at a phenomenal rate. We have a range and diversity of characters in our group and we always have a fun time together.
We operate a membership system and invite guests to join us &
column2: try us out first before enrolling as a full member.&nbsp
column3: Guests can attend two events only before we ask you to join our group as a ‘life member’.

column1: Our 'life members' enjoy access to our groups in Zurich, Geneva, Basel, Lugano &
column2: London. We are adding more cities in the future!

column1: New members wishing to join must be referred by an existing ‘founder member’ or ‘life member’ of our group.
We have our regular mid month networking event, lunches, brunches, dinners, city tours, bar tours, art events, comedy nights, club nights &
- Join in! Feel free to message us with any questions and we look forward to meeting you.

column2: never miss our news or an event:- www.facebook.com/zurichlgbtprofessionals

column1: Please ensure you have a face picture in your profile. We reserve the right to decline membership of our group if you do not have a clear face picture.
When requesting permission to join our group you need to include in your profile a link to one of your social media profiles. Either Linkedin, Facebook or Twitter.

column3: inactive members may be deleted from our group as we are a serious group for serious like minded people.&nbsp

column1: We look forward to meeting you soon!

12,LGBT,lgbt,Zürich,CH,1479755568000,"

Hello, this Meetup is for anyone who dreams of, interested in the idea of, plans to, wants terribly to... share a house with other people under the rainbow flag. It means living fully and openly as who you are, regardless of sexual orientation, gender expression, underwear color. I have had several house sharing experiences, and I love it. I just wish I could live with LGBTQ people and their allies. As this is more fun!!
This Meetup is to get people who are interested in this idea to meet, talk about their project, their vision of a house, their lifestyle and rythme. I personally wish I would live in a house that welcomes languages such as english-german-french, non-smoking, with educated crowd, with an interest in living green and organic. But you might have your own idea of a house-share? Let's meet!!

Perhaps you’d like more quality non-sexual touch in your life, or perhaps you just love to cuddle at every opportunity. Come along, meet good people, learn about (and experience) the importance of touch, and have fun. Hold and Cuddle is a structured event which explores affection, intimacy, boundaries and verbal/non-verbal communication. The evening is strictliy non-sexual so that you can relax and
column2: meet men in a fun and warm-hearted environment.

Dann schau rein, triff tolle Männer, erfahre, lerne, erlebe die Wichtigkeit von Körperberührungen, Körperkontakt und fühl Dich einfach wohl.

12,LGBT,lgbt,Sankt Gallen,CH,1504468687000,"

Wenn du an einem Treffen kommen möchtest, bitten wir dich an der Versanstaltung mit Gesichtsfoto und Namen anzumelden, wir möchten sehen, wer es ist, der/die kommen möchte.

Du kannst selber bei deinen Profileinstellungen hier einstellen, ob man deine Interessen sehen kann oder nicht, das ist dir überlassen. Das ist eine private Gruppe, d.h. interessierte Meetup Mitglieder können den Inhalt dieses Meetups nur teilweise einsehen, bevor sie beitreten. Nicht-Mitglieder
column3: Veranstaltungsorte, Beschreibungen, Mitgliederlisten, Gruppenprofile, Teilnehmer, Fotos oder andere geteilte Inhalte. Datenschutz, Verbindlichkeit ist uns wichtig.

column1: Unsere Geschichte: Am Herbst 2017 waren wir hier in St Gallen ein schwuler Mann und eine Bi Frau, die sich noch von Zürich aus gekannt haben, und sie haben beide das Bedürfnis gehabt, zusammen durch Gebet in ihrem persönlichem Leben gestärkt zu werden.
column2: Beide sind von evangelikalem, sprich pfingstlichem, charismatischem Hintergrund, sie kamen informell an der Militärkantine in St. Gallen an einer Bank sitzend zusammen um zu beten.<span>&nbsp
column3: Sie kannten ähnliche, LGBT christliche Gruppen in anderen Städten, in der ""Zwischenraum"" Bewegung aber eben noch nicht in St Gallen, oder in der Ostschweiz.&nbsp
column4: Sie meinten, es wäre doch schön ein regelmässiges Treffen, bzw. Community für ähnlich gesinnte zu haben. So kam es dann zur meetup Gründung, und dann kam es zum ersten Treffen im September 2017 mit erst 3, am zweiten mal 7 Leuten, Frauen und Männer, der Rest ist Geschichte.

column1: Die Vision ist eine christliche LGBT Gruppe in St Gallen zu haben, die im Gebet ihren Fokus hat, uns gegenseitig im Glauben, in Christus zu stärken, und Jünger sein. Genau :)

12,LGBT,lgbt,Zürich,CH,1426692533000,"

This is a group for LGBT Professionals in Zurich who wish to meet other LGBT's for networking, sharing ideas, good conversation and making new friends.
We are the largest most active mixed international group in Switzerland and we welcome Lesbian, Gay, Bisexual &
column2: Transgender. We bring all LGBT Professionals together!

column1: We meet every month at a cool venue, normally on the third Wednesday or Thursday of each month.
Our group was founded in March 2015. Since then we have grown at a phenomenal rate. We have a range and diversity of characters in our group and we always have a fun time together.
We operate a membership system and invite guests to join us &
column2: try us out first before enrolling as a full member.&nbsp
column3: Guests can attend two events only before we ask you to join our group as a ‘life member’.

column1: Our 'life members' enjoy access to our groups in Zurich, Geneva, Basel, Lugano &
column2: London. We are adding more cities in the future!

column1: New members wishing to join must be referred by an existing ‘founder member’ or ‘life member’ of our group.
We have our regular mid month networking event, lunches, brunches, dinners, city tours, bar tours, art events, comedy nights, club nights &
- Join in! Feel free to message us with any questions and we look forward to meeting you.

column2: never miss our news or an event:- www.facebook.com/zurichlgbtprofessionals

column1: Please ensure you have a face picture in your profile. We reserve the right to decline membership of our group if you do not have a clear face picture.
When requesting permission to join our group you need to include in your profile a link to one of your social media profiles. Either Linkedin, Facebook or Twitter.

column3: inactive members may be deleted from our group as we are a serious group for serious like minded people.&nbsp

column1: We look forward to meeting you soon!

column2: Queer* Menschen am Montagabend zwei Bahnen zum freien Schwimmen an. Alle Geschlechter und Geschlechtsidentitäten sind willkommen – unabhängig von Transitionsstand oder Transitionsabsichten. Fühlt euch frei, jene Badebekleidung zu tragen, in der ihr euch am wohlsten fühlt, ob Lycra-Shirt oder weite Badehose ist einerlei! Hauptsache, keine Strassenbekleidung.

12,LGBT,lgbt,Zürich,CH,1479755568000,"

Hello, this Meetup is for anyone who dreams of, interested in the idea of, plans to, wants terribly to... share a house with other people under the rainbow flag. It means living fully and openly as who you are, regardless of sexual orientation, gender expression, underwear color. I have had several house sharing experiences, and I love it. I just wish I could live with LGBTQ people and their allies. As this is more fun!!
This Meetup is to get people who are interested in this idea to meet, talk about their project, their vision of a house, their lifestyle and rythme. I personally wish I would live in a house that welcomes languages such as english-german-french, non-smoking, with educated crowd, with an interest in living green and organic. But you might have your own idea of a house-share? Let's meet!!

Perhaps you’d like more quality non-sexual touch in your life, or perhaps you just love to cuddle at every opportunity. Come along, meet good people, learn about (and experience) the importance of touch, and have fun. Hold and Cuddle is a structured event which explores affection, intimacy, boundaries and verbal/non-verbal communication. The evening is strictliy non-sexual so that you can relax and
column2: meet men in a fun and warm-hearted environment.

column1: Sehnst Du Dich manchmal auch nach nicht sexuellen Berührungen, sondern Geborgenheit, Gehalten Werden, Innigkeit? Oder vielleicht bist Du einfach ein Mann der gerne kuschelt – Kuschelbär? Dann schau rein, triff tolle Männer, erfahre, lerne, erlebe die Wichtigkeit von Körperberührungen, Körperkontakt und fühl Dich einfach wohl.

column2: Cuddle ist ein strukturierter Anlass an dem wir Zuneigung, Intimität, Grenzen erkennen und respektieren, gemeinsam entdecken und erleben. Hold &amp
column4: Du kannst Dich entspannen, Geben und Nehmen in spielerischer –&nbsp

12,LGBT,lgbt,Windisch,CH,1515623191000,"

Hello :) I am a gay woman from the UK, and I want to meet some people from the LGBT+ community who live in Aargau. I live in Windisch, near Brugg, with my German wife. I think it's important that we have more in common than just being LGBT+, and I imagine that we could find common activities, have discussions, and work on projects together. To start off, I would like to know who is interested and what your ideas are! I'm very friendly, and can speak English, German, and French.

Hoi! Ich bin eine lesbische Frau, die aus Grossbritannien kommt, und ich will Leute kennenlernen, die LSBTQ sind und in Aargau wohnen. Ich wohne in Windisch, neben Brugg, mit meiner deutschen Frau. Ich glaube, es ist wichtig, nicht nur LSBTQ Leute zu kennen, sondern auch weitere Gemeinsamkeiten zu haben, und ich stelle mir vor, dass wir gemeinsame Aktivitäten, Diskussionen, und Projekte machen könnten. Am Anfang, will ich einfach wissen, wen es gibt, und was eure Ideen sind! Ich bin sehr freundlich, und kann Englisch, Deutsch, und Französisch sprechen.

Welcome to our LGBT Social Club!! Are you new in town and don't know a soul? Maybe you just want to expand your social network/circle? Are you ready to shake up your social calendar and take your chance? Sign up! We are looking for some good peoples ready to bring their A-games! We encourage you to come out and network! Make new friends, date, mingle, post away, be involved! Are you not so keen on the bar scene? We can do another events like game nights, dinner, movie nights, hikes, comedy nights, whatever! Contribute your ideas! You might be surprised how many others share your interests!

12,LGBT,lgbt,Zürich,CH,1426692533000,"

This is a group for LGBT Professionals in Zurich who wish to meet other LGBT's for networking, sharing ideas, good conversation and making new friends.
We are the largest most active mixed international group in Switzerland and we welcome Lesbian, Gay, Bisexual &
column2: Transgender. We bring all LGBT Professionals together!

column1: We meet every month at a cool venue, normally on the third Wednesday or Thursday of each month.
Our group was founded in March 2015. Since then we have grown at a phenomenal rate. We have a range and diversity of characters in our group and we always have a fun time together.
We operate a membership system and invite guests to join us &
column2: try us out first before enrolling as a full member.&nbsp
column3: Guests can attend two events only before we ask you to join our group as a ‘life member’.

column1: Our 'life members' enjoy access to our groups in Zurich, Geneva, Basel, Lugano &
column2: London. We are adding more cities in the future!

column1: New members wishing to join must be referred by an existing ‘founder member’ or ‘life member’ of our group.
We have our regular mid month networking event, lunches, brunches, dinners, city tours, bar tours, art events, comedy nights, club nights &
- Join in! Feel free to message us with any questions and we look forward to meeting you.

column2: never miss our news or an event:- www.facebook.com/zurichlgbtprofessionals

column1: Please ensure you have a face picture in your profile. We reserve the right to decline membership of our group if you do not have a clear face picture.
When requesting permission to join our group you need to include in your profile a link to one of your social media profiles. Either Linkedin, Facebook or Twitter.

column3: inactive members may be deleted from our group as we are a serious group for serious like minded people.&nbsp

column1: We look forward to meeting you soon!

Hello, this Meetup is for anyone who dreams of, interested in the idea of, plans to, wants terribly to... share a house with other people under the rainbow flag. It means living fully and openly as who you are, regardless of sexual orientation, gender expression, underwear color. I have had several house sharing experiences, and I love it. I just wish I could live with LGBTQ people and their allies. As this is more fun!!
This Meetup is to get people who are interested in this idea to meet, talk about their project, their vision of a house, their lifestyle and rythme. I personally wish I would live in a house that welcomes languages such as english-german-french, non-smoking, with educated crowd, with an interest in living green and organic. But you might have your own idea of a house-share? Let's meet!!

Come along, meet good people, learn about (and experience) the importance of touch, and have fun. column2: meet men in a fun and warm-hearted environment.

12,LGBT,lgbt,Windisch,CH,1515623191000,"

Hello :) I am a gay woman from the UK, and I want to meet some people from the LGBT+ community who live in Aargau. I live in Windisch, near Brugg, with my German wife. I think it's important that we have more in common than just being LGBT+, and I imagine that we could find common activities, have discussions, and work on projects together. To start off, I would like to know who is interested and what your ideas are! I'm very friendly, and can speak English, German, and French.

Hoi! Ich bin eine lesbische Frau, die aus Grossbritannien kommt, und ich will Leute kennenlernen, die LSBTQ sind und in Aargau wohnen. Ich wohne in Windisch, neben Brugg, mit meiner deutschen Frau. Ich glaube, es ist wichtig, nicht nur LSBTQ Leute zu kennen, sondern auch weitere Gemeinsamkeiten zu haben, und ich stelle mir vor, dass wir gemeinsame Aktivitäten, Diskussionen, und Projekte machen könnten. Am Anfang, will ich einfach wissen, wen es gibt, und was eure Ideen sind! Ich bin sehr freundlich, und kann Englisch, Deutsch, und Französisch sprechen.

Welcome to our LGBT Social Club!! Are you new in town and don't know a soul? Maybe you just want to expand your social network/circle? Are you ready to shake up your social calendar and take your chance? Sign up! We are looking for some good peoples ready to bring their A-games! We encourage you to come out and network! Make new friends, date, mingle, post away, be involved! Are you not so keen on the bar scene? We can do another events like game nights, dinner, movie nights, hikes, comedy nights, whatever! Contribute your ideas! You might be surprised how many others share your interests!

12,LGBT,lgbt,Zürich,CH,1426692533000,"

This is a group for LGBT Professionals in Zurich who wish to meet other LGBT's for networking, sharing ideas, good conversation and making new friends.
We are the largest most active mixed international group in Switzerland and we welcome Lesbian, Gay, Bisexual &
column2: Transgender. We bring all LGBT Professionals together!

column1: We meet every month at a cool venue, normally on the third Wednesday or Thursday of each month.
Our group was founded in March 2015. Since then we have grown at a phenomenal rate. We have a range and diversity of characters in our group and we always have a fun time together.
We operate a membership system and invite guests to join us &
column2: try us out first before enrolling as a full member.&nbsp
column3: Guests can attend two events only before we ask you to join our group as a ‘life member’.

column1: Our 'life members' enjoy access to our groups in Zurich, Geneva, Basel, Lugano &
column2: London. We are adding more cities in the future!

column1: New members wishing to join must be referred by an existing ‘founder member’ or ‘life member’ of our group.
We have our regular mid month networking event, lunches, brunches, dinners, city tours, bar tours, art events, comedy nights, club nights &
- Join in! Feel free to message us with any questions and we look forward to meeting you.

column2: never miss our news or an event:- www.facebook.com/zurichlgbtprofessionals

column1: Please ensure you have a face picture in your profile. We reserve the right to decline membership of our group if you do not have a clear face picture.
When requesting permission to join our group you need to include in your profile a link to one of your social media profiles. Either Linkedin, Facebook or Twitter.

column3: inactive members may be deleted from our group as we are a serious group for serious like minded people.&nbsp

column1: We look forward to meeting you soon!

Hello, this Meetup is for anyone who dreams of, interested in the idea of, plans to, wants terribly to... share a house with other people under the rainbow flag. It means living fully and openly as who you are, regardless of sexual orientation, gender expression, underwear color. I have had several house sharing experiences, and I love it. I just wish I could live with LGBTQ people and their allies. As this is more fun!!
This Meetup is to get people who are interested in this idea to meet, talk about their project, their vision of a house, their lifestyle and rythme. I personally wish I would live in a house that welcomes languages such as english-german-french, non-smoking, with educated crowd, with an interest in living green and organic. But you might have your own idea of a house-share? Let's meet!!

Perhaps you’d like more quality non-sexual touch in your life, or perhaps you just love to cuddle at every opportunity. Come along, meet good people, learn about (and experience) the importance of touch, and have fun. Hold and Cuddle is a structured event which explores affection, intimacy, boundaries and verbal/non-verbal communication. The evening is strictliy non-sexual so that you can relax and
column2: meet men in a fun and warm-hearted environment.

column1: Sehnst Du Dich manchmal auch nach nicht sexuellen Berührungen, sondern Geborgenheit, Gehalten Werden, Innigkeit? Oder vielleicht bist Du einfach ein Mann der gerne kuschelt – Kuschelbär? Dann schau rein, triff tolle Männer, erfahre, lerne, erlebe die Wichtigkeit von Körperberührungen, Körperkontakt und fühl Dich einfach wohl.

column2: Cuddle ist ein strukturierter Anlass an dem wir Zuneigung, Intimität, Grenzen erkennen und respektieren, gemeinsam entdecken und erleben. Hold &amp

12,LGBT,lgbt,Sankt Gallen,CH,1504468687000,"

Wenn du an einem Treffen kommen möchtest, bitten wir dich an der Versanstaltung mit Gesichtsfoto und Namen anzumelden, wir möchten sehen, wer es ist, der/die kommen möchte.

Du kannst selber bei deinen Profileinstellungen hier einstellen, ob man deine Interessen sehen kann oder nicht, das ist dir überlassen. Das ist eine private Gruppe, d.h. interessierte Meetup Mitglieder können den Inhalt dieses Meetups nur teilweise einsehen, bevor sie beitreten. Nicht-Mitglieder
column3: Veranstaltungsorte, Beschreibungen, Mitgliederlisten, Gruppenprofile, Teilnehmer, Fotos oder andere geteilte Inhalte. Datenschutz, Verbindlichkeit ist uns wichtig.

column1: Unsere Geschichte: Am Herbst 2017 waren wir hier in St Gallen ein schwuler Mann und eine Bi Frau, die sich noch von Zürich aus gekannt haben, und sie haben beide das Bedürfnis gehabt, zusammen durch Gebet in ihrem persönlichem Leben gestärkt zu werden.
column2: Beide sind von evangelikalem, sprich pfingstlichem, charismatischem Hintergrund, sie kamen informell an der Militärkantine in St. Gallen an einer Bank sitzend zusammen um zu beten.<span>&nbsp
column3: Sie kannten ähnliche, LGBT christliche Gruppen in anderen Städten, in der ""Zwischenraum"" Bewegung aber eben noch nicht in St Gallen, oder in der Ostschweiz.&nbsp
column4: Sie meinten, es wäre doch schön ein regelmässiges Treffen, bzw. Community für ähnlich gesinnte zu haben. So kam es dann zur meetup Gründung, und dann kam es zum ersten Treffen im September 2017 mit erst 3, am zweiten mal 7 Leuten, Frauen und Männer, der Rest ist Geschichte.

column1: Die Vision ist eine christliche LGBT Gruppe in St Gallen zu haben, die im Gebet ihren Fokus hat, uns gegenseitig im Glauben, in Christus zu stärken, und Jünger sein. Genau :)

12,LGBT,lgbt,Zürich,CH,1426692533000,"

This is a group for LGBT Professionals in Zurich who wish to meet other LGBT's for networking, sharing ideas, good conversation and making new friends.
We are the largest most active mixed international group in Switzerland and we welcome Lesbian, Gay, Bisexual &
column2: Transgender. We bring all LGBT Professionals together!

column1: We meet every month at a cool venue, normally on the third Wednesday or Thursday of each month.
Our group was founded in March 2015. Since then we have grown at a phenomenal rate. We have a range and diversity of characters in our group and we always have a fun time together.
We operate a membership system and invite guests to join us &
column2: try us out first before enrolling as a full member.&nbsp
column3: Guests can attend two events only before we ask you to join our group as a ‘life member’.

column1: Our 'life members' enjoy access to our groups in Zurich, Geneva, Basel, Lugano &
column2: London. We are adding more cities in the future!

column1: New members wishing to join must be referred by an existing ‘founder member’ or ‘life member’ of our group.
We have our regular mid month networking event, lunches, brunches, dinners, city tours, bar tours, art events, comedy nights, club nights &
- Join in! Feel free to message us with any questions and we look forward to meeting you.

column2: never miss our news or an event:- www.facebook.com/zurichlgbtprofessionals

column1: Please ensure you have a face picture in your profile. We reserve the right to decline membership of our group if you do not have a clear face picture.
When requesting permission to join our group you need to include in your profile a link to one of your social media profiles. Either Linkedin, Facebook or Twitter.

column3: inactive members may be deleted from our group as we are a serious group for serious like minded people.&nbsp

column1: We look forward to meeting you soon!

12,LGBT,lgbt,Zürich,CH,1479755568000,"

Hello, this Meetup is for anyone who dreams of, interested in the idea of, plans to, wants terribly to... share a house with other people under the rainbow flag. It means living fully and openly as who you are, regardless of sexual orientation, gender expression, underwear color. I have had several house sharing experiences, and I love it. I just wish I could live with LGBTQ people and their allies. As this is more fun!!
This Meetup is to get people who are interested in this idea to meet, talk about their project, their vision of a house, their lifestyle and rythme. I personally wish I would live in a house that welcomes languages such as english-german-french, non-smoking, with educated crowd, with an interest in living green and organic. But you might have your own idea of a house-share? Let's meet!!

Perhaps you’d like more quality non-sexual touch in your life, or perhaps you just love to cuddle at every opportunity. Come along, meet good people, learn about (and experience) the importance of touch, and have fun. Hold and Cuddle is a structured event which explores affection, intimacy, boundaries and verbal/non-verbal communication. The evening is strictliy non-sexual so that you can relax and
column2: meet men in a fun and warm-hearted environment.

column1: Sehnst Du Dich manchmal auch nach nicht sexuellen Berührungen, sondern Geborgenheit, Gehalten Werden, Innigkeit? Oder vielleicht bist Du einfach ein Mann der gerne kuschelt – Kuschelbär? Dann schau rein, triff tolle Männer, erfahre, lerne, erlebe die Wichtigkeit von Körperberührungen, Körperkontakt und fühl Dich einfach wohl.

column2: Cuddle ist ein strukturierter Anlass an dem wir Zuneigung, Intimität, Grenzen erkennen und respektieren, gemeinsam entdecken und erleben. Hold &amp

12,LGBT,lgbt,Windisch,CH,1515623191000,"

Hello :) I am a gay woman from the UK, and I want to meet some people from the LGBT+ community who live in Aargau. I live in Windisch, near Brugg, with my German wife. I think it's important that we have more in common than just being LGBT+, and I imagine that we could find common activities, have discussions, and work on projects together. To start off, I would like to know who is interested and what your ideas are! I'm very friendly, and can speak English, German, and French.

Hoi! Ich bin eine lesbische Frau, die aus Grossbritannien kommt, und ich will Leute kennenlernen, die LSBTQ sind und in Aargau wohnen. Ich wohne in Windisch, neben Brugg, mit meiner deutschen Frau. Ich glaube, es ist wichtig, nicht nur LSBTQ Leute zu kennen, sondern auch weitere Gemeinsamkeiten zu haben, und ich stelle mir vor, dass wir gemeinsame Aktivitäten, Diskussionen, und Projekte machen könnten. Am Anfang, will ich einfach wissen, wen es gibt, und was eure Ideen sind! Ich bin sehr freundlich, und kann Englisch, Deutsch, und Französisch sprechen.

12,LGBT,lgbt,Genève,CH,1504043665000,"

Calling all queer runners! We are a new LGBTQ group that organises running sessions for people of any fitness level, in diverse locations in and around Geneva. The group is an official member of the worldwide Frontrunners organisation for gay, lesbian, bisexual, trans, intersex, and queer-identifying people who are enthusiastic about jogging.

Meetup training sessions will be once or twice per week (possibly less in winter) and flexible in terms of distance and speed. Occasional trail running on Saleve and in the Jura is also scheduled for the warmer months.

All meetup training sessions are logged using the MapMyRun application and shared on our Facebook profile geneva.frontrunners.3

https://www.facebook.com/geneva.frontrunners.3
Participation is voluntary. Frontrunners claims no liability for injuries or accidents that may occur during club activities and events. Insurance is the responsibility of participants / members.

Projet D (Plateforme Romande de Jeunes pour l’Egalité et la Diversité) est un groupe de jeune créé pour les jeunes LGBT (Lesbiens, Gays, Bi et Trans) de 20 à 30 ans. Projet D organise des apéros, des soirées dans un bar ou en boites, des activités sportives et des sorties culturelles. Elle a pour but de créer des opportunités de rencontre pour favoriser l’échange et la convivialité entre les jeunes LGBT de 18 à 30 ans. Projet D réalise également des débats et des projets politiques relatifs à la question de genre ou l’orientation sexuelle. N’hésite pas ! 12,LGBT,lgbt,Zürich,CH,1426692533000,"

This is a group for LGBT Professionals in Zurich who wish to meet other LGBT's for networking, sharing ideas, good conversation and making new friends.
We are the largest most active mixed international group in Switzerland and we welcome Lesbian, Gay, Bisexual &
column2: Transgender. We bring all LGBT Professionals together!

column1: We meet every month at a cool venue, normally on the third Wednesday or Thursday of each month.
Our group was founded in March 2015. Since then we have grown at a phenomenal rate. We have a range and diversity of characters in our group and we always have a fun time together.
We operate a membership system and invite guests to join us &
column2: try us out first before enrolling as a full member.&nbsp
column3: Guests can attend two events only before we ask you to join our group as a ‘life member’.

column1: Our 'life members' enjoy access to our groups in Zurich, Geneva, Basel, Lugano &
column2: London. We are adding more cities in the future!

column1: New members wishing to join must be referred by an existing ‘founder member’ or ‘life member’ of our group.
We have our regular mid month networking event, lunches, brunches, dinners, city tours, bar tours, art events, comedy nights, club nights &
- Join in! Feel free to message us with any questions and we look forward to meeting you.

column2: never miss our news or an event:- www.facebook.com/zurichlgbtprofessionals

column1: Please ensure you have a face picture in your profile. We reserve the right to decline membership of our group if you do not have a clear face picture.
When requesting permission to join our group you need to include in your profile a link to one of your social media profiles. Either Linkedin, Facebook or Twitter.

column3: inactive members may be deleted from our group as we are a serious group for serious like minded people.&nbsp

column1: We look forward to meeting you soon!

Hello, this Meetup is for anyone who dreams of, interested in the idea of, plans to, wants terribly to... share a house with other people under the rainbow flag. It means living fully and openly as who you are, regardless of sexual orientation, gender expression, underwear color. I have had several house sharing experiences, and I love it. I just wish I could live with LGBTQ people and their allies. As this is more fun!!
This Meetup is to get people who are interested in this idea to meet, talk about their project, their vision of a house, their lifestyle and rythme. I personally wish I would live in a house that welcomes languages such as english-german-french, non-smoking, with educated crowd, with an interest in living green and organic. But you might have your own idea of a house-share? Let's meet!!

Perhaps you’d like more quality non-sexual touch in your life, or perhaps you just love to cuddle at every opportunity. Come along, meet good people, learn about (and experience) the importance of touch, and have fun. Hold and Cuddle is a structured event which explores affection, intimacy, boundaries and verbal/non-verbal communication. The evening is strictliy non-sexual so that you can relax and
column2: meet men in a fun and warm-hearted environment.

Contribute your ideas! You might be surprised how many others share your interests!

12,LGBT,lgbt,Zürich,CH,1426692533000,"

This is a group for LGBT Professionals in Zurich who wish to meet other LGBT's for networking, sharing ideas, good conversation and making new friends.
We are the largest most active mixed international group in Switzerland and we welcome Lesbian, Gay, Bisexual &
column2: Transgender. We bring all LGBT Professionals together!

column1: We meet every month at a cool venue, normally on the third Wednesday or Thursday of each month.
Our group was founded in March 2015. Since then we have grown at a phenomenal rate. We have a range and diversity of characters in our group and we always have a fun time together.
We operate a membership system and invite guests to join us &
column2: try us out first before enrolling as a full member.&nbsp
column3: Guests can attend two events only before we ask you to join our group as a ‘life member’.

column1: Our 'life members' enjoy access to our groups in Zurich, Geneva, Basel, Lugano &
column2: London. We are adding more cities in the future!

column1: New members wishing to join must be referred by an existing ‘founder member’ or ‘life member’ of our group.
We have our regular mid month networking event, lunches, brunches, dinners, city tours, bar tours, art events, comedy nights, club nights &
- Join in! Feel free to message us with any questions and we look forward to meeting you.

column2: never miss our news or an event:- www.facebook.com/zurichlgbtprofessionals

column1: Please ensure you have a face picture in your profile. We reserve the right to decline membership of our group if you do not have a clear face picture.
When requesting permission to join our group you need to include in your profile a link to one of your social media profiles. Either Linkedin, Facebook or Twitter.

column3: inactive members may be deleted from our group as we are a serious group for serious like minded people.&nbsp

column1: We look forward to meeting you soon!

12,LGBT,lgbt,Zürich,CH,1479755568000,"

Hello, this Meetup is for anyone who dreams of, interested in the idea of, plans to, wants terribly to... share a house with other people under the rainbow flag. It means living fully and openly as who you are, regardless of sexual orientation, gender expression, underwear color. I have had several house sharing experiences, and I love it. I just wish I could live with LGBTQ people and their allies. As this is more fun!!
This Meetup is to get people who are interested in this idea to meet, talk about their project, their vision of a house, their lifestyle and rythme. I personally wish I would live in a house that welcomes languages such as english-german-french, non-smoking, with educated crowd, with an interest in living green and organic. But you might have your own idea of a house-share? Let's meet!!

Perhaps you’d like more quality non-sexual touch in your life, or perhaps you just love to cuddle at every opportunity. Come along, meet good people, learn about (and experience) the importance of touch, and have fun. Hold and Cuddle is a structured event which explores affection, intimacy, boundaries and verbal/non-verbal communication. The evening is strictliy non-sexual so that you can relax and
column2: meet men in a fun and warm-hearted environment.

column1: Sehnst Du Dich manchmal auch nach nicht sexuellen Berührungen, sondern Geborgenheit, Gehalten Werden, Innigkeit? Oder vielleicht bist Du einfach ein Mann der gerne kuschelt – Kuschelbär? Dann schau rein, triff tolle Männer, erfahre, lerne, erlebe die Wichtigkeit von Körperberührungen, Körperkontakt und fühl Dich einfach wohl.

column2: Cuddle ist ein strukturierter Anlass an dem wir Zuneigung, Intimität, Grenzen erkennen und respektieren, gemeinsam entdecken und erleben. Hold &amp

12,LGBT,lgbt,Windisch,CH,1515623191000,"

Hello :) I am a gay woman from the UK, and I want to meet some people from the LGBT+ community who live in Aargau. I live in Windisch, near Brugg, with my German wife. I think it's important that we have more in common than just being LGBT+, and I imagine that we could find common activities, have discussions, and work on projects together. To start off, I would like to know who is interested and what your ideas are! I'm very friendly, and can speak English, German, and French.

Hoi! Ich bin eine lesbische Frau, die aus Grossbritannien kommt, und ich will Leute kennenlernen, die LSBTQ sind und in Aargau wohnen. Ich wohne in Windisch, neben Brugg, mit meiner deutschen Frau. Ich glaube, es ist wichtig, nicht nur LSBTQ Leute zu kennen, sondern auch weitere Gemeinsamkeiten zu haben, und ich stelle mir vor, dass wir gemeinsame Aktivitäten, Diskussionen, und Projekte machen könnten. Am Anfang, will ich einfach wissen, wen es gibt, und was eure Ideen sind! Ich bin sehr freundlich, und kann Englisch, Deutsch, und Französisch sprechen.

Welcome to our LGBT Social Club!! Are you new in town and don't know a soul? Maybe you just want to expand your social network/circle? Are you ready to shake up your social calendar and take your chance? Sign up! We are looking for some good peoples ready to bring their A-games! We encourage you to come out and network! Make new friends, date, mingle, post away, be involved! Are you not so keen on the bar scene? We can do another events like game nights, dinner, movie nights, hikes, comedy nights, whatever! Contribute your ideas! You might be surprised how many others share your interests!

12,LGBT,lgbt,Zürich,CH,1426692533000,"

This is a group for LGBT Professionals in Zurich who wish to meet other LGBT's for networking, sharing ideas, good conversation and making new friends.
We are the largest most active mixed international group in Switzerland and we welcome Lesbian, Gay, Bisexual &
column2: Transgender. We bring all LGBT Professionals together!

column1: We meet every month at a cool venue, normally on the third Wednesday or Thursday of each month.
Our group was founded in March 2015. Since then we have grown at a phenomenal rate. We have a range and diversity of characters in our group and we always have a fun time together.
We operate a membership system and invite guests to join us &
column2: try us out first before enrolling as a full member.&nbsp
column3: Guests can attend two events only before we ask you to join our group as a ‘life member’.

column1: Our 'life members' enjoy access to our groups in Zurich, Geneva, Basel, Lugano &
column2: London. We are adding more cities in the future!

column1: New members wishing to join must be referred by an existing ‘founder member’ or ‘life member’ of our group.
We have our regular mid month networking event, lunches, brunches, dinners, city tours, bar tours, art events, comedy nights, club nights &
- Join in! Feel free to message us with any questions and we look forward to meeting you.

column2: never miss our news or an event:- www.facebook.com/zurichlgbtprofessionals

column1: Please ensure you have a face picture in your profile. We reserve the right to decline membership of our group if you do not have a clear face picture.
When requesting permission to join our group you need to include in your profile a link to one of your social media profiles. Either Linkedin, Facebook or Twitter.

column3: inactive members may be deleted from our group as we are a serious group for serious like minded people.&nbsp

column1: We look forward to meeting you soon!

12,LGBT,lgbt,Zürich,CH,1479755568000,"

Hello, this Meetup is for anyone who dreams of, interested in the idea of, plans to, wants terribly to... share a house with other people under the rainbow flag. It means living fully and openly as who you are, regardless of sexual orientation, gender expression, underwear color. I have had several house sharing experiences, and I love it. I just wish I could live with LGBTQ people and their allies. As this is more fun!!
This Meetup is to get people who are interested in this idea to meet, talk about their project, their vision of a house, their lifestyle and rythme. I personally wish I would live in a house that welcomes languages such as english-german-french, non-smoking, with educated crowd, with an interest in living green and organic. But you might have your own idea of a house-share? Let's meet!!

12,LGBT,lgbt,Windisch,CH,1515623191000,"

Hello :) I am a gay woman from the UK, and I want to meet some people from the LGBT+ community who live in Aargau. I live in Windisch, near Brugg, with my German wife. I think it's important that we have more in common than just being LGBT+, and I imagine that we could find common activities, have discussions, and work on projects together. To start off, I would like to know who is interested and what your ideas are! I'm very friendly, and can speak English, German, and French.

Hoi! Ich bin eine lesbische Frau, die aus Grossbritannien kommt, und ich will Leute kennenlernen, die LSBTQ sind und in Aargau wohnen. Ich wohne in Windisch, neben Brugg, mit meiner deutschen Frau. Ich glaube, es ist wichtig, nicht nur LSBTQ Leute zu kennen, sondern auch weitere Gemeinsamkeiten zu haben, und ich stelle mir vor, dass wir gemeinsame Aktivitäten, Diskussionen, und Projekte machen könnten. Am Anfang, will ich einfach wissen, wen es gibt, und was eure Ideen sind! Ich bin sehr freundlich, und kann Englisch, Deutsch, und Französisch sprechen.

12,LGBT,lgbt,Sankt Gallen,CH,1504468687000,"

Wenn du an einem Treffen kommen möchtest, bitten wir dich an der Versanstaltung mit Gesichtsfoto und Namen anzumelden, wir möchten sehen, wer es ist, der/die kommen möchte.

Du kannst selber bei deinen Profileinstellungen hier einstellen, ob man deine Interessen sehen kann oder nicht, das ist dir überlassen. Das ist eine private Gruppe, d.h. interessierte Meetup Mitglieder können den Inhalt dieses Meetups nur teilweise einsehen, bevor sie beitreten. Nicht-Mitglieder
column3: Veranstaltungsorte, Beschreibungen, Mitgliederlisten, Gruppenprofile, Teilnehmer, Fotos oder andere geteilte Inhalte. Datenschutz, Verbindlichkeit ist uns wichtig.

column1: Unsere Geschichte: Am Herbst 2017 waren wir hier in St Gallen ein schwuler Mann und eine Bi Frau, die sich noch von Zürich aus gekannt haben, und sie haben beide das Bedürfnis gehabt, zusammen durch Gebet in ihrem persönlichem Leben gestärkt zu werden.
column2: Beide sind von evangelikalem, sprich pfingstlichem, charismatischem Hintergrund, sie kamen informell an der Militärkantine in St. Gallen an einer Bank sitzend zusammen um zu beten.<span>&nbsp
column3: Sie kannten ähnliche, LGBT christliche Gruppen in anderen Städten, in der ""Zwischenraum"" Bewegung aber eben noch nicht in St Gallen, oder in der Ostschweiz.&nbsp
column4: Sie meinten, es wäre doch schön ein regelmässiges Treffen, bzw. Community für ähnlich gesinnte zu haben. So kam es dann zur meetup Gründung, und dann kam es zum ersten Treffen im September 2017 mit erst 3, am zweiten mal 7 Leuten, Frauen und Männer, der Rest ist Geschichte.

column1: Die Vision ist eine christliche LGBT Gruppe in St Gallen zu haben, die im Gebet ihren Fokus hat, uns gegenseitig im Glauben, in Christus zu stärken, und Jünger sein. Genau :)
